<?xml version="1.0"?>
<page xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
      xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:magento:framework:View/Layout/etc/page_configuration.xsd">
    <body>
        <!--
            Hyvä Checkout pickup-store picker mount (v1.3.0).

            Renders the picker card list at checkout.shipping.methods.before,
            i.e. immediately above the shipping-method radios. Clicking a
            card runs Alpine.js client-side, which finds the matching
            radio (etechflow_isp_<store_code>) and triggers click + change,
            which fires our ShippingAddressAutofillPlugin and tax-correct
            shipping address pre-fill.

            v1.3.0 — architectural refactor: dropped Magewire entirely.
            The v1.0.x – v1.2.x picker extended
            \Magewirephp\Magewire\Component directly, which doesn't
            participate in Hyvä Checkout's Magewire bootstrap pipeline
            (Hyvä Checkout only hydrates components implementing its
            form-abstraction interfaces). The block silently failed to
            mount on every install since v1.0.0. v1.2.1 fixed the
            container name; v1.3.0 fixes the actual hydration by replacing
            Magewire with plain server-render + Alpine.js, which Hyvä
            Checkout supports natively and which doesn't require any
            framework-specific bootstrap.

            v1.2.1 — corrected container name from `checkout.shipping.before`
            (doesn't exist) to `checkout.shipping.methods.before`. The
            container fix is retained because it's correct on its own
            — the v1.3.0 Block-based picker still mounts here.

            On stores without Hyvä Checkout (plain Hyvä Theme, Luma), this
            layout handle never triggers — those flows use the standard
            Magento shipping-method radio list (one radio per active
            store, from the carrier in Phase 6).
        -->
        <referenceContainer name="checkout.shipping.methods.before">
            <block class="ETechFlow\InStorePickup\Block\Checkout\PickupStorePicker"
                   name="etechflow.isp.checkout.pickup_store_picker"
                   template="ETechFlow_InStorePickup::checkout/pickup-store-picker.phtml"
                   before="-"/>
        </referenceContainer>
    </body>
</page>
